2. DEFINITIONS

To prevent immediate denial from all parties, the Institute defines the following technical terms:

Term	Definition
“Understands”	Generates statistically plausible language about a topic
“Reasons”	Produces structured text that resembles reasoning
“Knows”	Has seen similar text before
“Learns”	Was trained earlier and is now being rebranded
“Autonomous”	Requires a human but in a less visible way
“Human-level”	Performs well on carefully selected benchmarks
“Assist”	Does work you must check
“May”	Legal invisibility cloak
“Can”	Technically possible under non-chaotic conditions

These definitions are collectively known as the Marketing–Engineering Translation Table (METT).

