9. CONCLUSION

This paper concludes the following simultaneously:
	•	AI is a tool.
	•	AI is marketed like a colleague.
	•	AI is priced like an employee.
	•	AI is legally a product.
	•	AI is technically a statistical model.
	•	AI is socially treated like an authority.
	•	AI companies are technology companies.
	•	AI companies are also advertising companies.
	•	The law is behind the marketing.
	•	The marketing is ahead of the engineering.
	•	The engineering is ahead of public understanding.
	•	Everyone is ahead of responsibility.

Therefore, responsibility will be assigned later, retroactively, after the first large-scale Reasonable Reliance Event (RRE), also known as “the court case that changes all the terms of service.”

⸻

Final Statement of the Institute:

If a machine is marketed as a tool, people use it carefully.
If a machine is marketed as intelligent, people trust it.
If a machine is trusted, mistakes become liability.
If liability exists, someone eventually pays.

The only unanswered question is:

Who, exactly, was the reasonable one?

